I '''Abu-Nuwas al-Hasan ben Hani al-Hakami''' ([[756 in poetry|756]]–[[814 in poetry|814]]),<sup id="fn_a_back">[[#fn a|a]]</sup> a kilala murin king lagyung '''Abū-Nuwās'''<ref name="Gp2">[[#GA|Garzanti]]</ref> ({{lang-ar|ابونواس}}; {{lang-fa|ابونواس}}, ''Abu Novas''), metung ya kareng mapyang diling klasikong [[Arabic poetry|Arabu]]ng poeta o watas, a sinulat muring poesyang [[Persian poetry|Persian]] kareng aliwang pamikatagun. Mibait ya king lakanbalen o ciudad ning [[Ahvaz]] king [[Persian Empire|Persia]], king tatang a [[Arabu]] ampong imang [[Persian people|Persian]], <ref name="Gp2"/> megi yang matenakan kareng eganaganang uri ning poesyang Arabu. Linub ne i Abu Nuwas king tradisyong [[folkloric]], at linto yang mapilang ukdu o besis king ''[[Aklat da reng Libu ampong Metung a Bengi]]''.(The Book of One Thousand and One Nights).

